    <para styleclass="Heading2_atoc_"><text styleclass="Heading2_atoc_" translate="true">Select Model Files</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Selecting </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Model Files|Select Model Files</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> or clicking </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Select files for the archive</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> on the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Files" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Files</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> pane</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> is a convenient way to add model input, output, and ancillary files to the archive structure. The user selects a directory and ModelArchiver searches that directory and its subdirectories for files that have extensions recognized by ModelArchiver. It will then open the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Model_Files_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Model Files</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box in which the user can fine-tune which files are added to the archive structure.</text></para>
